                <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan> Rubrius Onesimus sibi et Mari<lb break="no" n="2"/>ae Arabinae uxori et suis vivos <note>sic</note> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ecit</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/>excipitur <expan><abbr>hui</abbr><ex>c</ex></expan> sepulchro iu<supplied reason="lost">s</supplied> itus am<lb break="no" n="4"/>biti ex ceteris partibus q<supplied reason="lost">u</supplied>oque <lb n="5"/>versus per pedes centenos <lb n="6"/>hoc <expan><abbr>sepulchr</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>hered</abbr><ex>es</ex></expan> non seq<expan><ex>u</ex><abbr>et</abbr><ex>ur</ex></expan>
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Vorderer Teil eines Urnenkastens; in mehrere Teile gebrochen. Inschriftfeld in Form einer tabula ansata. Z. 1: Buchstaben D und M in den beiden ansae. Z. 7 (Ende): ET auf der Zeichnung bei Abramić nicht eingetragen; Lesung nach ILJug. (B): ILJug: Z. 5: quoque; Z. 7: herd(es) seq(u)et(ur); Abramić: Z. 7: non seq(uetur).</p>
            </div>
